description:
&lt;p&gt;The Priory Hospital Preston has established an excellent reputation for offering calming and recovery focused residential treatment for up to 38 service users.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking a recruit a highly motivated and committed Ward Manager for our 12-bedded adult Acute unit.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Key accountabilities for the role include;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;• Preferred experience working with an Acute setting&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;• Managing staffing ladders and staff roster&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;• Promoting and maintaining a professional working environment&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;• Ensuring a high standard of care at all times&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;• Providing leadership to staff in helping achieve unit objectives&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;• Ensure a high quality of patient care is provided.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The role holder will be a Registered Mental Health Nurse (RMN) with excellent communication skills ensuring effective communication within the multi-disciplinary team. Management qualification/experience and an up to date knowledge of regulatory requirements and outcomes is also required.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Hours of work will be 9am – 5pm Monday to Friday, however you will be required to cover shifts and work within the numbers as required.&lt;/p&gt;
